list.comment: Solve medium problem, find the first and l

task.summary: Default task

Solve medium and a bit tricky range interval problem, find the number of the smallest unoccupied chair given the arrival and leave time for all the person using greedy.
Levered prior learnings of solving range interval problems.
Add Lakoten interview experience for Equities trading developer.
Add another solution to find LCA of two nodes in a n-ary tree in SmallestCommonRegion using recursion.
Simplify optimized solution in ValidTriangleNumber using the same logic as ThreeSumSmaller

Solve medium assignment problem, find the optimal assignment pattern such that each student gets one mentor and each mentor gets one student using backtracking and bitmasking.
Also update CampusBikes with the possibility of greedy being a wrong approach to solve the problem.
Learnings: Initially tried solving the problem using greedy during contest, got WA, switched to backtracking.

Solve medium problem, find the largest number that can be generating after mutating a substring using greedy.
Learnings: Leveraged prior learning of solving similar string mutation problem LargestOddNumberInString
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, given various intervals and a color, find the final sum of the colors at each index using prefix sum.

Solve medium problem, find the total sum of all the keys that starts with a prefix using Trie.
Leveraged prior learning of storing useful information directly in trie node.
Add hint to understand Euclidean algorithm to find GCD
Add DP State optimization solution for FormLargestNumberWithDigitsThatSumUpToTarget
Fix typo and simplify code in PredictTheWinner
Add comment on why greedy approach works in CampusBikes
Solve medium problem, perform level order traversal on a n-ary tree using BFS
Solve easy problem, count no of negative numbers in a row and column sorted matrix using two pointers.

Solve medium and a bit tricky to understand problem, find whether a move is legal or not by iterating in 8 directions.
Was unable to solve this question in the contest as I wrongly assumed that the endpoint must end on the border :(
Solve easy problem, find whether a prefix of given arrays of words can result in a target string using two pointers.

Solve medium problem and a bit tricky to optimize runtime, remove maximum stones to minimize the total using greedy / priority queue or bucket/counting sort.
Learnings: Counting sort can be used to optimize runtime when we are interested only in min/max.

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, reorder an array such that every adjacent pair of elements equals [x, 2*x] using greedy.
Learnings: Reading the problem statement carefully is very important. Lately I have been misreading them quite a lot, which is costing me a lot :(
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the min cost to flip a string to monotone increasing using two pass solution.
Solve medium and a bit tricky maths problem, find the min steps required to find the first floor at which an egg breaks given 2 eggs and N floors using maths or DP

Solve hard and extremely tricky to optimize, find the first floor at which egg breaks given n floors and k eggs using DP + Binary Search
Learnings: DP State Optimization problem as the trivial DP gives TLE.
Solve easy and a bit tricky problem, find the peak index in a mountain array using binary search.

Solve hard and a bit tricky problem, find the last day when you can still reach any cell in last row from any cell in first row using Union Find with Dummy Node as an optimization.
Learnings: Using dummy node in Union Find is a cool technique to quickly find whether a group of cells is connected to another group of cells.

Solve medium problem, find the first unique number in a queue using LRU Cache or TreeSet
Leveraged prior learnings of implementing LRU Cache using dummy head/tail nodes.
Solve medium problem, check whether a root to leaf path exists in a binary tree that matches the target path using recursion.
Add premium tag to FirstUniqueNumber

Solve medium problem, find the maximum product achieved by splitting a binary tree into two subtrees by removing one edge using DP
Leveraged prior learnings of solving tree partitioning problems that the decision to cut should be made by the parent.

Solve medium problem, find the sum of the provided intervals given that you can update the value at any index using segment tree
Learnings: Finally implemented segment tree after brushing it aside for so long.

Solve medium and extremely tricky problem, find the number of ways to reach a target node in minimum cost in a graph using djikstra + dp
Learnings: DP on graphs are quite tricky problems. Need to carefully handle overflow cases.
Add related problem in AllPathsFromSourceToTarget
Solve medium problem, verify whether the provided string can represent a valid preorder traversal of a binary tree using recursion.
Add related tree partitioning problems
Solve medium problem, given a shift array and a string, return a transformed string where the first (i+1) characters are shifted shift[i] times using suffix sum.
Solve medium problem, find the maximum average value of a subtree of a binary tree using postorder traversal.
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, given an array find the longest length of set of elements where s[i] = {a[i], a[a[i]], a[a[a[i]]], ...} using dp on graphs

Solve medium and extremely tricky problem, reconstruct a 2 row binary matrix given the sum of elements of first row and last row along with the column sum of each column using greedy.
Learnings: In greedy reconstruction problems, try to first fill what is known and does not have any choice

Solve medium and extremely tricky problem, find the longest uncommon subsequence between a list of strings such that the subsequence exists only in one string and not in any other string using greedy and brute force.
Solve easy but a bit tricky problem, find the intersection of all rectangles originating from [0,0] using greedy.

Solve hard and extremely tricky problem, given an array, add minimum elements to the array to cover all the numbers in the range of [1,target] by subset sums of the elements of the array using greedy.
Leveraged prior learnings of solving the smallest impossible subset sum.
Solve medium and extremely tricky problem, find the max number of consecutive subset sum possible using greedy.
Solve medium problem, find the first and last occurrence of all groups of land using two pass DFS.

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the number of pairs which are strictly weaker than any other pairs using binary search and greedy.
This would be a really fun interview problem.
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, given two grids, find the number of islands in grid2 where all the corresponding cells in grid1 are also part of an island using two pass DFS.
Add approach to solve the FindAllGroupsOfFarmland in one pass.
Solve medium and implementation heavy problem, perform locking and unlocking operations on a binary tree using DFS.
Add related DP subsequences problems similar to RussianDollEnvelopes and tag DistinctSubsequences2 with DP State Optimization
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the total no of arithmetic subarrays of length >= 3 using maths.

Solve easy problem, find the winner of a tic-tac-toe game by tracking the number of moves made by a player for each row, column, diagonal and anti-diagonal
Learnings: Computing the diagonalId for all the diagonals was a bit tricky as it required correct handling of negative id's. Fixed the code of DesignTicTacToe by using correct diagonalId's.
Add time complexity to multi BFS solution of WallsAndGates
